snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp: I am the ARTISTIC male perspective and I do agree with the Mera and Power Rangers perspective. WB wants to make the characters way more detailed with their wardrobe but sometimes fans want it TONED DOWN. For example if Catwoman made a 2017 debut she would be preferred with a basic leather or latex jumpsuit and most likely we'd end up with a movie version of her with a carbon fiber jumpsuit with cat emblems all over. The issue is WB thinks the characters need more details and some fans want the characters to look a little bit basic. As a male I really don't mind for SOME characters to be more revealing but we should put some logic in it, what if Wonder Woman debuted in a star covered blue leotard and Harley Quinn wearing a corset with blue & red booty shorts. Sometimes sexy doesn't mean revealing look at Tim Burton's gorgeous Catwoman (Michelle Pfeifer) and compare it to Halle Berry's Catwoman. I love Halle Berry but that suit was a disaster.

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp: Olá. Gosto muito do canal de vcs, parabéns. Eu sou muito fã do Johnny e fiquei muito triste com a noticia da agressão. Se o Johnny o fez espero que pague, mas eu acredito que ele mereça uma segunda chance, pois é a primeira vez que isso acontece, inclusive a mãe dos filhos dele o defendeu, a primeira esposa dele tb disse que ele não é agressivo, mas muito gentil. Só que o ser humano não é perfeito. Ele pode ter tido um momento de extresse e acontecido tal fato. Confesso que alguns detelhes dessa história ainda me soam um pouco estranhas, mas o Johnny é um ótimo ator, é um dos melhores que eu já vi, e não gostaria que um erro estragasse uma vida toda de talento por cada personagem que ele fez até  hoje com tanta dedicação. O que eu percebo é que as pessoas jugam de mais. Espero que tudo se resolva o mais rápido possível e que ele possa da a volta por cima com todos os problemas que estam acontecendo na vida dele e refletindo na sua carreira.

Slowly melting!

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp: Nobody but Amber and Johnny lived behind closed doors with each other but them. The only thing I can comment on is what I saw in this video. I saw a man enraged at the woman. I saw the woman recording the man and asking questions of him. We do not know if there was abuse by Johnny to Amber and she felt frustrated to the point of wanting to record him to get outsiders to believe her. We do not know if she was the abuser to him during their time together and he felt frustrated and lashed out in this video. I have my gut feeling but I cannot prove it. What I would say is that ANYONE who starts to get abused by another, there is only 1 way to handle it. GET AWAY AND GO NO CONTACT IMMEDIATELY IT STARTS!

I say this because many of us who watch vids on narcissistic abuse were indeed abused. If Amber was an abuse victim but is tough enough to stand up to her "abuser," hell she'd have been out of there six months into the relationship. They would have never gotten married.  He was the victim and it's unfortunate that he stayed so long and got to that point. Anyway I'm not trying to be mean or dismiss you but that old "mind your business" argument really can't apply on an awareness of abuse channel.  It's hard for all of us to call out our abusers and speak our truth but that is the best way to survive AND stay no contact. Which yes, you are DEAD ON about. No Contact is truly the Only Way Out. snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp: This is what I go through almost every day with my roommate. I am Johnny Depp (although I raise my voice I don't get violent anymore as I once did before I quit alcohol), and she is Amber Heard. If only you could see Amber's face. I swear I see total satisfaction in my roommate when she is gaslighting and playing her little games. These people can seriously effect you so bad psychologically that you begin to think you're insane. What sucks in reality, most times than not these people have very low self-esteem, are insecure and are incapable of loving themselves or anyone else. The mask they wear, the games they play, they are all to protect their fragile egos. I have to fight feeling guilty because of taking the blinders off (went to counseling, quit drinking alcohol) after 12 years of friendship and finding out she's not who I thought she was, haha neither was I. I always took the blame most times, not even knowing if I was to blame (massive confusion), just to make it stop. I spent over a decade of being an enabler/co-dependent. She's not who she thinks she is. A false self is better than no self? I think not. It's the authentic self, warts and all, that I found helped me find myself. It's not easy facing one's demons, but it's even harder thinking you've got a chance to control or make others face their own. It is with a heavy and sad heart that I have realized I will have to eventually go "NO CONTACT" :(

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp:
I have reported Clean Bodies' comment for accusing me of "deflection," as well as still more verbal abuse on a genuine victim of narc abuse. Never mind that Johnny Depp is famous and probably doesn't have time to watch these videos let alone read the comments. It's the principle of the thing. I will not, in the future, put up with ANY MORE comments, and I mean any kind, suggesting Johnny Depp here is the abuser. I will not have it. I have done enough explaining and reiterating my research regarding this situation and how it relates to narc abuse. Some of you have shown an interest in at least listening to both sides of Heard's allegations. In turn, I have been happy to at least discuss it with you. However, when someone posts a troll comment that's nothing but hateful accusations at best, insults at worst, that's where I draw the line. Someone accuses me of deflection, i .e. enabling a narc and deflecting it back to the so-called victim...thank you, no. I've had enough gaslighting and deflection by narcs in my life, I don't need it on my video channel, thank you much. :) I'm sorry if this makes some of you uncomfortable but there are times you have to call it out for what it is. I have deleted Clean Bodies' comment and will delete any other FUTURE comments from those accusing Johnny Depp of narc abuse. I will not debate about anything else I've written in this comment either. Bottom line, for the sakes of all of our sanities? There has been enough confusion. Anyone still on the fence or unsure can research more about covert narcissists as well as overt narcissists and the various different traits they exhibit. I intend to make a video on covert narcissism in the next few days but meanwhile, feel free to research it. It's simply time to stay focused, and while all of our recoveries are different, it just doesn't help to post too much hate or fear with NO research whatsoever.
Thank you, and I now return you to our regularly scheduled programming. :) Namaste, Kate

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp:
I was raised by a histrionic narc mother prone to hitting.. which caused me to hit in school.. I had a bad temper most of my life.. until my daughter was born and I was so intellectually committed to not yelling or escalating in front of my child.. It was like having chains taken off me.. if my wife was messing with me emotionally.. gas lighting whatever.. it just didn't seed with my daughter around me.. for the first time in my life I felt like I have a reason "not" to engage.. the interesting thing is my new passive demeanor drove my wife crazy and wherein when I would flip out before and she would yield.. after my daughter she used my daughter as krptonite.. she would hold her in her arms and just berate and curse me knowing I wouldn't fight back. she never spoke to me like that before.. but with my baby in her arms it was like a game to see how much she could get away with saying.. really strange.. but she's an ex now and my daughter 16 yrs.( just yesterday actually)
is my best friend.. and totally aware that "grammy" and her mother are nutty.. my biggest difficulty is to teach her not to be affected by those who affect others for sport.. to not be affected by Grammy who's shrill affect leave you thinking she will snap at any moment.. it's hard to make her aware but also keep her from hating.
these people are very difficult to navigate.

But re video.. yeah she's baiting but he's got some issues as well.. his behavior is not the easiest to defend.. especially when he's hours away from whatever happened.. I could understand his reactions much better if it were during an incident.. but to be that worked up hours later.. dude.. smoke a joint.. wtf

hey man.. yeah when I first stumbled onto information one thing I noticed is that there wasn't anybody saying how to heal.. which if you think about it.. that's pretty fucking bizzar.. every ailment under the sun has some snake oil guy saying do this or do that.. it took me days of searching before I found a couple.. husband wife.. they had a website and some books published.. their story was wife Caucasian.. husband maybe Latin of some sort.. could have been Greek.. good looking wife was to. So she had been dealing with his weird behavior for quite awhile and then she had children and had enough but she loved the dude.. so she went looking for answers.. very similar to myself sans the marriage part.. she finally got a diagnosis but no treatment..
finally she found a psychotherapist who had a course of action.. but she had to get husband on board.. the most difficult part right.. gave him ultimatum..
you come with me to this Dr or me and kids are leaving you.. period.. he went.
The treatment first revolved around honesty.. the whole thing sounded reasonable..
Treatment started with focusing each day one by one on truth. he had to tell the truth. it was fascinating.. it went on from there with his history being analyzed and answers within his upbringing that helped him understand.. and the bottom line was that at the very beginning and when I found them they had books published and an extensive Web site.. they are partners in the whole thing.. as I remember it wasn't like "cured".. it was more like alcoholism or something.. where he followed rules that were obviously different than his instincts.. but the marriage had lasted years and she said for the most part he was a changed man.

I hear what your saying.. I know they say impossible to make an adjustment but I don't go for blanket conclusions like that.. there's too much in history wherein those fatalistic ideas were published only to have professionals take different approaches.. it's all about the person.. if you can trace it back to a bad upbringing.. which the girl I knew cried many times on my shoulder about being treated bad as a child.. plus she's in a health field profession.. msw social worker.. if touch can get that person to person to respect the Dr treating her/their case.. and you can get them to believe "this is what happens being raised in this environment." and you can get them to follow the rules.. baby steps.. day by day honesty (which for me is at the heart of the whole thing.. denial and dishonesty.) get them to understand that they won't be judged.. I mean the 2 that I know.. it's like they are constantly shaping reality.. time serving.. to fend off perceived humiliation and thinking they have to manipulate to get outcomes they want.. it's constant worry.. constant feeling judged.. do you know how taxing that must be.. to think you have to be perfect all the time.. to be wound so tight you can't just acknowledge when you've stumbled.. what a fucking burden.

What do just remember now re that couple is they said that you have tear the person down.. they have to be willing to go back to the point of trauma.. usually be a parent not loving or some really painful shit.. they have to go back into that and feel it.. which is what they didn't do when young.. they created a way not to feel it.. so they have to feel it and be crushed and only then build themselves back up which was going to be a long process involving people who truly loved him wife kids ect.. and therapy.. but he was willing and that's what he did.

It all makes perfect sense.. I think psychologist say they can't fix it out of frustration because they need the truth to do their job.. This Dr said that is the main problem.. and that it has to be a therapist who knows how to ask the right questions and know what bullshit and what's not.. I went to a psychologist with her.. she lied her ass off.. totally revised the history.. time spans all kinds of shit.. I couldn't understand why she made the appointments.. but in speaking with him alone he had no awareness of recent info on the condition so I just stopped.. I knew more than him at that point.

But her making the appointments among many other things contradict mainstream perceptions like they are totally aware.. I honestly don't think she was.. and that's based on not only my perception but objective evidence.. her making appointment with psychology department connected to her job.. wherein I could have told them horrible shit about her.. but she believed her own bullshit.. it became her reality.. another thing is it scared her.. like she knew something was not right.. and she'd just go death stare.. and there were times I'd tell her she does certain things and she'd say "I don't want to do that.. and you could see that it was a struggle.. Anyway I'll get back at you.. I'm tried to get my settings right personal messages.. you have to go to persons channel and click something.. anyway I'll check setting and see if possible.

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp: Wow, I'm really glad to see this -- I have had so much guilt over the way I let my anger spill over a couple of times when my narc had done terrible things to me.  He used those episodes to paint me as the unstable crazy person, even though neither instance was at all premeditated, and I never hurt anyone.  I see so much of how I felt in Depp's behavior, and in his place (were I male, that is, sadly) I have no doubt I'd be suffering the same kind of media abuse.

replies.comments:
[{'kind': 'youtube#comment', 'etag': 'AeyoNxY2C_X3nEZo-pwd3BB_6bo', 'id': 'Ugii-IQLqG7-qngCoAEC.8VRZByzguTJ8VSA3OS16gI', 'snippet': {'videoId': '78d_G_rB56U', 'textDisplay': '+Tulan Zoya, thank you! That means a lot. Yes, Johnny Depp...he's been in the public eye for so long and has had a lot of "scandals" where he was misrepresented and misunderstood. What I've seen so far from him is an amazing freedom and happiness that he never had during his marriage. I went to see him perform with Hollywood Vampires twice last year, and he just was like a kid in a candy store. He loves music and the opportunity to play it. I guess narc victims have some kind of mental bond that extends all over, even if we've never met. Those of us who are smeared and gaslighted but still have to survive in life...we know the signs of recovery when we see it...as well as abuse. I just keep praying for Johnny throughout this, but I feel like he's got this handled, bless him. He does have a good strong friendship circle as well as family and work colleagues. I was really moved when his co-stars from Pirates and Jerry Bruckheimer spoke up for him about his so-called " conduct" on set. They all said he was professional, on time, and always generous, dedicated to the character and working with the others. They would know! Lol. Johnny's got this. I'm just glad to stand up for him whenever I get the opportunity, since, unfortunately, it's still a hot topic that never really goes away. Millions of others like me who have spoken out have banded together that way. You probably know all this but when Johnny won the People's Choice award this year, he thanked the people for standing by him and trusting him. He was almost in tears. That was so amazing, and I felt like we had all sort of come together in a "family" even though we never met the man lol.
Yes, it does get hard, when people lash out at either me or anyone else who defends him as a narc abuse survivor. I feel so many are just programmed to be "politically correct" and how "dare" anyone doubt a woman's allegations of violence, etc. That would be a good argument in many cases, but these days too many women abuse that. These are narc women of course, and it's so premeditated...just set the man up, go out of your way to make him angry, then call him abusive. It sucks because a lot of women in the past used to be told "You asked for it" or "you provoked him." I hated that argument then and I still do. But? In a narc's case, female or male? They DO provoke. We have our responsibilities for our actions, but I'm not talking about actions. Narcs provoke bad feelings in us, psychological trauma and issues. What we do with those issues is different for all, but...at any rate, I hope this world eventually gets some awareness about narcs and what they do to try to bring us to our breaking points...and use it against us. Ugh! You sound like you've had a tough time with narcs, same with me. All we can do is stay focused on our lives, and not give too much energy to what we hear in backlash. There's a lot of people still not wanting to believe that narcs exist whether it's about Johnny Depp or anyone else. :D Lmao. It's up to those of us who have been there, and may still be there...to keep raising our voices. :) Thanks so much, Tulan, keep in touch and I wish you all the best in your journey. Namaste! snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp: Thank-you for sharing this,,,, i experienced 6 months of this last year between January to June, in 2016. It's been just over a year since i ended the daily mental & emotional torture which can't even be classed as a relationship but in the year between June last year an now, i have received 8 hand written letters to my address. Threats from her relating to coming to my place of work, my photo uploaded onto a site called cheaters, which was discovered by someone who Googled me. Continued attempts at contacting me with messages an requests to contact her on new phones everytime i block the old numbers, via my family members i.e. my younger brother, aunt an a cousin whom i've probably only spoken to 3 times in my life. She tried to also use the cleaners at my workplace as flying monkies by telling them to tell me she loves me just last month, which after all the twisted things she has said to my aunt about me and all the abuse she has said or messaged to me previously shows how Narcissistic this individual is. Luckily, i have a record of every single bit of abuse, message, letter dates of her contacting others to get to me and her attempts to contact me. Not to mention the countless withheld phones i have received in the last year. It's only because of her 4 children why i have not arranged for an injunction, which would mean getting police involved. Because of her narcissist disorder, she would just be fuelled by any attention/ acknowledgment of her stalking, manipulation an harassment. Just yesterday, she messaged me from 2 new numbers wishing me a belated happy birthday, apologising that it would of been sooner had she been able to obtain my number previously, as were some long lost friends an i would somehow welcome this intrusion into my life, which has been a now relentless 13 month campaign. Sadly, at this point i think it will have to be dealt with legally for this woman to get the message and maybe get some profressional help. Can imagine there are tons of men & women out there experiencing similar or maybe worst situations, but aren't even aware that the person they are dealing with is a narcissist.

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp:
I just saw an amazing video that I need to share with everyone. Especially those who watched Johnny Depp's behavior on this video and thought that HE was the narc. The reality is, however...Johnny's explosive anger and yelling at Amber is part of what a lot of victims do when it just gets to be too much. They don't know what to do and they're totally confused by what the narc is doing to them. They lose their ability to think rationally, because they're always questioning what the narc says about them being "crazy," or whatnot. They begin to exhibit behavior of a "crazy person," and worse, the same behavior of the narcissist! Johnny Depp, had he been able to see things for what they were earlier on, I am sure he'd have gotten out WAY before this episode where he lost control and exploded on the cabinet door, the cabinets, walking around cursing, etc. It would not have happened. I am not condoning losing control of one's anger by any means. Because it eats at us when it happens. We literally start behaving like someone we're not. I feel, if anything that Johnny and Amber's relationship became a battle of emotional abuse towards each other. Johnny would react by emotionally abusing Amber in almost the same way she did him. God forbid this but I've heard of relationships where the narc victim WILL become violent with the narcissist. This only gives the narcissist power. I still see no proof that that happened with Johnny and Amber, but my point is this. GET OUT before that happens to you. GET OUT and break contact with the narcissist, before you get so beaten down you snap and can't take it anymore. Victims don't "become" narcissists by any means, BUT, we can "act" like a narcissist in our retaliation against a narc abuser. It is my hope that mine and other videos like the one I'm going to link here, help victims to RUN, DON'T WALK, away from their abusers, to avoid getting in so deep we do things we would never, ever do otherwise.
Thank you to the woman who runs the channel "From Surviving To Thriving," for this AMAZING eye-opener that victims and survivors MUST see.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A7VscEfi2ds

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp: Hi, Joseph, I just watched your two videos about Johnny's divorce and I must say that I'm extremely shocked at the number of things you got right about AH and what she did to him without knowing anything about any of them. I've been a fan of his for almost 15 years and I'm proud to say that I didn't believe anything she said not even for a second. First, because I know my idol and I know he would never be capable of hurting a woman, let alone a woman he was in love with. And second, because I have this thing since I was a child that kind of warns me, that kind of tells me when something bad is happening or about to happen with people I love.  And I had been feeling an extremely heavy vibration, which lasted for almost a year, unfortunately, coming from Johnny and AH whenever I looked at them together, but it got really worse when I looked at her alone. And judging by the bad energy I felt coming from their relationship and especially from her and based on what I know about this thing I have, I could tell, I understood that she was about to cause, or even already causing a lot of damage and suffering in his life. About three days before the divorce, I felt a very strong sensation that he needed prayers and help. I even told some people what I had been feeling and some of them laughed at me, saying I was just being a jealous fangirl. Oh God, I WISH it was jealousy, but unfortunately, I was right.  I'm sorry for writing this long comment, but could you please do a reading about if the truth will ever come out completely? I know he's innocent and I never needed proof of anything or anyone telling me she lied to know that he is the victim here, (he even proved his innocence in court) but I mean, will the truth that she faked everything finally be completely revealed? I don't know, maybe someone of her circle telling the media the details of her set up, or maybe a member of her family or even the billionaire guy that she is dating now? (She'll never confess, that is obvious). Because, of course that billionaire knows what she did to Johnny, and I have a feeling that she'll try to accuse him of something too. But he's not Johnny Depp. Johnny was an angel towards her, staying in silence during the circus she caused. I even believe that with the number of evidence he had against her, he could have put her in jail for lying about DV if he wanted, but he would never do that, of course. But THAT guy, judging by the bad vibration I feel coming from him, he will turn her life into hell if she tries something against him. Could you also do a reading about Johnny's case against those thieves from TMG and if she is involved in it? I personally have a feeling that she is. Thanks for the great video and once again, sorry for the extremely long comment.

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp:
Johnny Depp Refuses to Pay Amber Heard More Money in Divorce: She’s Trying to ‘Extend Her 15 Minutes of Fame Amber Heard and Johnny Depp‘s bitter divorce saga continues.

In new court documents obtained by PEOPLE, Depp is
accusing Heard of desperately clinging to the spotlight by requesting
for their divorce settlement to be reopened after they previously reached an agreement in August.

The 30-year-old actress filed a Request for Order motion with the court on Dec. 30 to enforce the $7 million settlement, which was to be donated to charity.

Heard claimed in the documents, “Johnny has not lived
up to his obligation to me under the [settlement], including payments,
allowing me to retrieve my personal property, transferring title of a
vehicle to me and meeting regarding division of the furniture and
furnishings in the residential units we occupied.”

The actress said she was eager to end her marriage.

She concluded, “Johnny has delayed the resolution of this matter. I want my life back. I want to be divorced now.”

Depp’s lawyer Laura Wasser, however, is challenging
the motion in court. In the documents filed Dec. 30, she claims Heard’s
request is “a blatant attempt to extend her fifteen minutes of fame” and
“an embarrassing grab for additional and unwarranted attorney’s fees.”

Before Christmas, Depp’s legal team filed new court documents demanding Heard pay him
$100,000 toward his attorneys’ fees and costs after the actress filed
the “entirely unnecessary” Request for Order earlier in the month.

The Rum Diary costars became embroiled in a
nasty court battle in May, when the actress filed to end her 15-month
marriage to Depp and accused him of domestic abuse.

Depp’s lawyers have previously called Heard’s
behavior throughout their divorce proceedings into question, stating
that she’s acted “erratically” and “uncooperatively.”

“The impact of her relentless pursuit on Johnny — the
damage her false allegations have caused his personal and professional
reputation, his and his family’s emotional well-being, and his finances
appears to be of no interest to Amber,” state the documents.

Depp also claims that Heard has continuously violated their confidentiality agreement “almost weekly.”

In November, Heard partnered with the #GirlGaze Project for a new video about domestic violence, and briefly shared her personal story, but did not mention Depp by name.

“Amber wants to maintain the media’s attention and thereby preserve her own fleeting relevance,” Depp’s latest filing claims.

A court hearing on the motion is scheduled for Jan. 13.

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp: Yes the video is very funny, and Depp's comments after the video was made prove 100% that he meant nothing that he said, possibly because it wasn't him facing any criminal charges but rather his wife was. Yes, Barnaby Joyce has a reputation here in Australia for being, I guess you could say direct, with his language and there was criticism at the time for the way he handled it, but Depp broke the law and didn't even have to go to court. That's probably why he's got an attitude of "I'm a big time celebrity and so I can break the law and get away with it." whereas his wife is more subdued.
snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textOrig: Yes the video is very funny, and Depp's comments after the video was made prove 100% that he meant nothing that he said, possibly because it wasn't him facing any criminal charges but rather his wife was. Yes, Barnaby Joyce has a reputation here in Australia for being, I guess you could say direct, with his language and there was criticism at the time for the way he handled it, but Depp broke the law and didn't even have to go to court. That's probably why he's got an attitude of "I'm a big time celebrity and so I can break the law and get away with it." whereas his wife is more subdued.

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp: É engraçado como em tantas vezes Amber Heard é vista como "a coitada". Johnny bebe a muito tempo e todo mundo sabia, menos a pobre mulher que sofreu agressão doméstica. Eu vou defender ele SIM! Do mesmo modo que a filha dele defendeu, e que a ex-esposa dele defendeu. Sabe de quem eu sinto nojo? Das pessoas que só vêem um lado, que não pesquisam uma outra parte da história, que julga pelo que a mídia fala. Ele tendo ou não se alterado, custava ela dar um tempo para ele? Em nenhum momento eu a vi ao lado dele apoiando, ajudando, em todo esse tempo eu nunca vi um sorriso sincero no rosto dele. Em todo relacionamento um é agressivo com outro quando está com a cabeça quente, Johnny está passando por momentos difíceis constantemente e perdeu a mãe não faz muito tempo mas, mesmo assim, vamos todos defender a linda "slim", a pobre Amber, a garota do iPhone na cara. Tenha dó!

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp:
Tara's death always bothered me, for several reasons:

1) I loved the character. She was shy and introverted but also very moral and decent and compassionate and had a more mature head on her shoulders. Whilst she wasn't an action go-getter like many of the characters she had a quiet strength about her that I really liked.

2) I didn't think the magic addiction storyline was handled well at all. It felt less like substance addiction and more like drunk on power. It was handled very weakly so Tara's death, which was being sold as this big dramatic moment, instead looked like the writers desperate to bring the season (which had limped along tbh) to some sort of big conclusion.

3) More than anything though, I do disagree with Amber on Joss' motives. She's says it wasn't done to hurt people, I think it was. I think Joss rather enjoys shocking and hurting the audience because he thinks the audience are willing masochists who enjoy the emotional pain he causes. What he didn't seem to understand was that whilst other deaths had some dramatic and emotional weight to them, this one had neither (indeed most of the elements were merely watered down re-hashes of previous seasons) and I think he is more annoyed that we aren't the willing masochists he assumed we were.

I honestly think that when you have a character who was blossoming, had more storylines that one could tell with them, who is well liked by fans and in a relationship which is groundbreaking and providing a positive message to people struggling, then it is utter madness to kill that character off for what was a very weak storyline.

I honestly think that when you have a character who was blossoming, had more storylines that one could tell with them, who is well liked by fans and in a relationship which is groundbreaking and providing a positive message to people struggling, then it is utter madness to kill that character off for what was a very weak storyline.

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp: Their relationship was definitely a gift to me. I remember watching the show every morning before school and I feel in love with Willow so fast. Like, first episode fast. I watched her fall in love with Oz and I was right there with her, (Buffy also sparked my love for Seth Green as well). But then I watched her fall in love with Tara and it was so exciting because I saw someone like me. I saw someone who fell in love with boys and girls, who fell in love with people, not genders. And still, over a decade later, I am head over heels for Willow xD I simultaneously want to be her and be with her. Her character was so well written and brilliantly portrayed by Alyson and her story arc blows me away every time I rewatch the show <3

I always felt like they just turned willow gay just to be cool and edgy since not too many shows don't have homosexual leads, but it came off as kinda forced, outta nowhere and way too soon after Oz. He was a big part of her and to all of a sudden have a new love interest so soon felt like an insult to him, especially how they just ran with it near the end of the show and just tossed in another lesbian gf for her like it was a trip to walmart.

I don't think any other character so easily shifted into relationships so soon compared to willow, I honestly think she shoulda just stayed singled for a good season or two after season 3.

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp:
Seeing Tara & Willow together (even if it's just the Actresses that play them) gave me a sort of satisfaction that I didn't expect to have. Still about W+T after all these years.
My Mom (who was very religious & yet was a BtVS fan before I was) was devasted when Oz left Willow & was like, "Well, now who's she gonna be with?!" & then we saw the connection with Tara & we were like, "Oh snap!" The funny thing about it is my Mom was homophobic. This show made her realize that it's not about being gay, it's about being loved & understood & accepted for who you are & what you do (which is why she loved the show so much). It was a very interesting thing to watch. And she loved the relationship between Tara & Willow. Rooted for it every week. I think she was more heartbroken than I was when her character was killed off.

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp: I think the reason why people dismisses POTC 2 is because of 3, I remember when Dead Man's Chest came out and everybody was comparing it to Empire Strikes Back and calling it among the best sequels ever created. at one point everyone thought Dead Man's Chest was going to surpass LOTR Return of the King & match up to Titanic box office but nearly came close at the time of 2006 scoring $1.066 billion at the box office. dead man's chest hands down is a great movie and not bad. a lot of people got upset with POTC 3 and likes to connect it with 2. Dead Man's Chest remains the highest-grossing live-action Walt Disney Pictures release. not counting the Marvel movies

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp:
FUN FACT: The ship young Jack is on at the beginning of the trailer is NOT the "Black Pearl", well not exactly. It is the "Wicked Wench" and Jack is not the original captain. You may also notice that the sails are not black. The ship eventually gets sunk and Jack makes a deal with Davy Jones to have it raised from the depths, renaming it the "Black Pearl".

I'm sure you know the rest of the story... ;)
snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textOrig:

I'm sure you know the rest of the story... ;)

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp: Agora entendo pq essa moça sofreu tantas acusações e o Depp usou do seu poder e riqueza para encobrir as acusações de violência doméstica que são comprovadamente reais contra a Amber. Ele perdeu toda a credibilidade com pessoas de bem, eu tinha um certo apreço por ele e seus trabalhos mas hoje olho pra ele e vejo um homem covarde e doente que perdeu a oportunidade de ser feliz ao lado de uma mulher fina, elegante, linda e inteligente. Não me surpreenderia se ela tiver virado lésbica por causa do trauma que vivenciou, como psicóloga compreendo o impacto negativo de uma relação assim. Por isso sempre evitei homens de grade poder aquisitivo, pois a maioria tem um rei na barriga e pior a sociedade apóia esses caras! Veja cmo os fãs de Depp se dirigem a ela. É nojento e violento. Mundo machista e decadente em que estamos vivendo e sabemos porque, as pessoas não investem em saúde emocional, pois se sentem auto-suficientes. Quantos pacientes atendi na área clínica durante alguns anos que se arrependem das atitudes e da conduta social que aderiram e para reverter as consequências de seus comportamentos, leva se uma década e em alguns casos é quase irreversível. Quanto maior a arrogância maior o estrago a si mesmo e ao meio que reside, naturalmente.

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp: Omg so you know how they say to turn your phones off during a movie at a theater? I was watching the Avengers 2 with my family on Memorial day sometime in 2015 I believe and everyone's phones started doing that. It was a tornado warning ⚠️ and since I'm the weather nerd in our family and had all the high tech apps at that time, my dad took my phone along with my brother outside the theater room into the hallway to check the radar. Long story short, we had to stay in that said theater for an hour after the movie ended, and then we hydroplaned our way home to find out that 70 plus people died in the flooding caused by that storm :(

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp:
I was skeptical about her armor in Justice League but also knew that Mera would not go into a fight with a skin tight suit. With that being said, even the scene in the Justice League trailer expressed a very blissful moment of her in the water. The most important thing was that it was believable that she could breath under water, just as it was believable that Superman didn't need to breath in space in BvS. I think Zack is going to do a good job capturing the art Atlantis and how it is relevant to DCEU while James Wan bring in a more grounded storyline.
DC is known for images that stick in your mind and really well written literature over a long period of time. Up until BvS, I was a firm believer that Zack should stay in the C.G.I. room. Then I noticed the care taken into transitioning Man of Steel to BvS, and that SH!T made me go back and watch Man of Steel and develop a whole new respect for how he treated the prototypical comic book character, of them all! The scene that still makes me say, "Holy Shit" is the flight scene. Beats audio, 4k, rewind that SH!T five times..... Now I wish I could fly around screwing with herds of animals! I had a great respect for the movie before due to how they treated the character progression of a kid being made to believe that he could change the world.
Some didn't agree with his death in BvS but Zack showed a talent of deconstructing comic book characters in The Watchmen. I asked myself "Why the Fuc|< would you deconstruct Superman?" Well, Jesus only became important after he sacrificed himself for humanity. Zack just paved the way for Superman to take his place as the prototype from the pages to the movies. Nobody, had seen hope for anything like the Fortress of Solitude taking place after Man of Steel. In the next Man of Steel, will we see the Kryptonian death ritual portrayed in the comics after Doomsday killed him? We may very well get a scene of the crystal like structures we've been waiting for. Not to mention that Krypton's council heavily resembled pages out of the Kryptonian death ritual and we've already seen Clark talking to Jonathan Kent's ghost.
Some bigger questions...... Unite the 7 was written in ads for the movie! Who's the Seventh they haven't revealed yet? Does Darkseid have Supergirl? Is Green Lantern involved or will we see the Martian Manhunter? The last two characters could have minimal involvement in the Justice league movie, if none at all. We already know that Kara has had a prequel comic to Man of Steel and an easter egg scene.
I would just like to say "Thank you DCEU for taking your proper place in comic book movies and treating it with the same respect that gave birth to you being bigger than Marvel. Please make Lex eat a sandwhich and start working out and God please make him sound like he went through puberty at one point... I know you're going to resurrect Superman, but would love to know how your going to bring Clark back to life... It's disturbing that Alfred's voice in the BvS trailer was thought to sound like the perfect Lex voice. I concur, it did! "

Grace, keep up the good work.

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp:
Well, she's missing her headdress, but otherwise I agree, the costume looks amazing. But one thing I've always wondered: Of what use is long hair under water? Do we know of any other hairy sea mammals? I'm all about red heads, true enough, but logically Mera should be Baldy McBaldBald.

Beyond that, however, I, too, am trepidatious about Amber Heard in this role. However cast her seems to have made the same mistake folks keep making with Susan Storm, casting hot little twinkles instead of someone who emotional maturity, poise, and grace. The Invisible Woman should have been Charlize Theron; Mera should have been Christina Hendricks. But who knows, maybe we'll get lucky and Hendricks will show up one day as Hawkwoman.

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp:
I really like both costumes, and think that her Justice League costume is her battle armor. The photo from Snyder, like all of his photos, has extremely dark filters, while if you notice the behind the scenes footage all shows that their costumes are cosplay/comics-correct in real life. Man of Steel's Superman costume looked blue-black and shiny, thanks to color correction. The behind the scenes footage showed bright blue and red on the costume instead.
tl;dr: i love all the costumes, and wish Zack would stop ALWAYS seeing the world Through A Filter Darkly (get it?)

the most immediate ways to brighten up the DCEU are exactly what Patty Jenkins did in Wonder Woman: play with all the colors, instead of just mud and concrete
snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textOrig:
I really like both costumes, and think that her _Justice League_ costume is her battle armor. The photo from Snyder, like all of his photos, has extremely dark filters, while if you notice the behind the scenes footage all shows that their costumes are cosplay/comics-correct in real life. Man of Steel's Superman costume looked blue-black and shiny, thanks to color correction. The behind the scenes footage showed bright blue and red on the costume instead. 
tl;dr: i love all the costumes, and wish Zack would stop ALWAYS seeing the world Through A Filter Darkly (get it?)

the most immediate ways to brighten up the DCEU are exactly what Patty Jenkins did in Wonder Woman: play with all the colors, instead of just mud and concrete

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp: I feel like the DCEU's making a massive comeback. Considering all its flaws, I still liked Dawn of Justice and think that it was criticised too harshly. That being said, the DCEU under Geoff Johns' control, is looking so much more promising; Wonder Woman looks like a gorgeously shot and graded film and the dynamic between the actors just works for me and things like this Mera costume just looks awesome. Part of movie magic, particularly with comic book films, is that it puts drawings into a real-life context and the DCEU is doing just fine.
snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textOrig: I feel like the DCEU's making a massive comeback. Considering all its flaws, I still liked Dawn of Justice and think that it was criticised too harshly. That being said, the DCEU under Geoff Johns' control, is looking so much more promising; Wonder Woman looks like a gorgeously shot and graded film and the dynamic between the actors just works for me and things like this Mera costume just looks awesome. Part of movie magic, particularly with comic book films, is that it puts drawings into a real-life context and the DCEU is doing just fine.

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp: Too green. Too much color. Much prefer JL colors, battle armor notwithstanding. She looks like a Disney character or a character out of the 90's Batman movies (and god forbid DCEU reverts to that style of color, pizazz, and humor - it's what DC finally got away from with success). Snyder has the colors and the movies tonally correct (it's just that he lacks Nolan's nuances in balancing inspiration with seriousness, but that's a different discussion and we're talking about colors here). I absolutely loved the colors of Krypton in MOS - it made it believable. Don't get cute and turn this into the Little Mermaid.
snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textOrig: Too green. Too much color. Much prefer JL colors, battle armor notwithstanding. She looks like a Disney character or a character out of the 90's Batman movies (and god forbid DCEU reverts to that style of color, pizazz, and humor - it's what DC finally got away from with success). Snyder has the colors and the movies tonally correct (it's just that he lacks Nolan's nuances in balancing inspiration with seriousness, but that's a different discussion and we're talking about colors here). I absolutely loved the colors of Krypton in MOS - it made it believable. Don't get cute and turn this into the Little Mermaid.

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp: I agree with Grace 100 percent here. That's freaking Mera, that thing that Zack gave us was more dull, grayed out visuals, sucking the very life out of what a CBM should look like. This Mera is vibrant and colorful, just like the ocean she comes from. This gives me high hopes for the possible visual styling's  of the Aqua Man movie. The movie should be alive with color, especially in the ocean parts. Atlantis should be a sight to behold. It's a shame that Zack got to get first crack at establishing the look of so many of these characters. Luckily for us, CBM's are known for changing their look from one film to the next.

snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textDisp:
"Λ" is not an A, it is the Greek letter Lambda, equivalent to L.
It was the central symbol on Sparta's shields. In nuclear physics it represents the function of 'half-life' in radio-decay. The lower-case "λ" was prominently featured in the game "Half-Life." It is used in several fields of mathematics as a symbol for a rate of change.
snippet.topLevelComment.snippet.textOrig:
"Λ" is not an A, it is the Greek letter Lambda, equivalent to L. 
It was the central symbol on Sparta's shields. In nuclear physics it represents the function of 'half-life' in radio-decay. The lower-case "λ" was prominently featured in the game "Half-Life." It is used in several fields of mathematics as a symbol for a rate of change.
